FT  07 JUN 93 / International Company News: China to invest in Haeco
maintenance arm
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CHINA'S aviation admin-istration will invest in the mainland aircraft
maintenance business of Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering (Haeco), AP-DJ
reports from Hong Kong.
The Civil Aviation Administration of China will buy 9 per cent of Taikoo
(Xiamen) Aircraft Maintenance, according to Haeco.
Haeco did not say how much the aviation supervisor will pay for the stake,
but said that total investment plans remained unchanged at USDollars 63m.
Haeco said that it held 61 per cent, adding in a statement that when the
deal was announced in March, it expected to own just 41 per cent.
Haeco added that it would sell up to 20 per cent of its holding to other
interested parties.
The company indicated that the 9 per cent portion for the Civil Aviation
Administration has been carved out of this 20 per cent.
Haeco is about 44 per cent owned by Swire Pacific, the Hong Kong
conglomerate which controls Cathay Pacific Airways. Cathay owns 35 per cent
of Hong Kong Dragon Airlines, which has many routes in China.
