FT  07 JUN 93 / Malpratices at the BBC
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE BBC board of management will this week receive a report from an internal
inquiry into alleged malpractices in the awarding of external contracts in
BBC Television.
Allegations being investigated range from suggestions of gifts and favours
from contractors eager to do business with the corporation, to conflicts of
interest in the awarding of contracts.
The role of Mr Bob Pugh, who until recently was BBC Television's general
manager of administration and facilities management, has been looked at by
the inquiry.
Mr Pugh headed a department whose responsibilities included awarding
contracts to private contractors to carry out non-programme work for the BBC
 -a recent trend at the corporation.
The BBC said it could say nothing until the inquiry was complete other than
that allegations were being 'vigorously investigated'.
