FT  07 JUN 93 / Move on squatters
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT is to crack down on squatting, making it a criminal offence
with possible prison sentences for offenders, the Home Office said
yesterday.
At present, unless there is a smashed window or damage to a door or other
part of the property, or drug-taking or other criminal activity, police
cannot move in. The object of new legislation will be to make occupying
someone else's home or premises without permission an offence.
