Dolphin Junction near Slough, Berkshire.
Almost 80,000 passengers from the West Country and Thames Valley pass
through Paddington every day.
The disruption will affect InterCity services from south Wales, Bristol and
the West Country. Commuter routes affected are those from Oxford and the
Thames Valley, Reading, Newbury and Hungerford in Berkshire.
