<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUN 93 / Finance and the Family: Contradictory data on UK house
prices - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HOUSE prices in the UK fell by a seasonally adjusted 1.2 per cent in May,
according to the Halifax House Price Index. Prices had risen 1.4 per cent in
March and 1.7 per cent in April. House prices are now 3.3 per cent below a
year ago, compared to last month's figure of 2.3 per cent down on the year.
But figures from the Nationwide building society this week showed a 1 per
cent rise in house prices in May, with prices down 5.5 per cent from a year
ago. The Halifax said that the housing market showed clear signs of
recovery, but warned that realistic prices were still necessary to generate
house sales. The Halifax predicts a gradual recovery in 1993, becoming more
sustained in 1994, when house prices should grow broadly in line with
earnings as a whole.
